serialization correlates with verb-final order, and "core" serialization with verb-medial order.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aOceanic languagesxGrammar. 0aOceanic languagesxSyntax. 0aOceanic languagesxVerb. 4aAustronesier. 4aSprache. 4aSprachtypologie. 4aWortstellung. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBril, Isabelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBril, Isabelle, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFrançois, Alexandre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLynch, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMargetts, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMosel, Ulrike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoyse-Faurie, Claire, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNæss, Åshild, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOzanne-Rivierre, Françoise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOzanne-Rivierre, Françoise, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPaia, Mirose, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReinig, Jessika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRivierre, Jean-Claude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoss, Malcolm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSenft, Gunter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVernaudon, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle 